      "writtenOn": "2026-06-10T18:23:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e What you are asking for requires Alexander to write a kernel driver with the new type. \n\nThis is not what I asked for, and i agree, a new kernel driver for this would be overkill assuming the one leg of TMP421 works.\n\nWe should add a new type that can use the TMP421 in the kernel, and just ignore one leg of it so we don\u0027t get errant readings.  Should just be a hwmontempsensor change to come up with a way to ignore the one leg of the TMP421 that isn\u0027t working.\n\nExposing a broken temp sensor that we know can\u0027t ever read doesn\u0027t seem right, and would be an openbmc bug for any system that has this card in it.",
      "parentUuid": "b02478f4_012a55e6",
